hworld.ws.about: This program is the original example hello world program downloaded from http://compsoc.dur.ac.uk/whitespace/examples.php

nerd.wsa.about: A simple example how to use the built-in Whitespace assembly language.

hmacro.wsa.about: An example how to use the standard library in the build-in Whitespace assembly language.

name.ws.about: This program will ask the users name and will display a personalized greeting. Downloaded from http://compsoc.dur.ac.uk/whitespace/name.ws.

quine.ws.about: This quine is written by Benjamin Lerman and was downloaded from http://compsoc.dur.ac.uk/whitespace/contrib.php.

fibonacci.ws.name: Fibonacci
fibonacci.ws.about: This Fibonacci calculator is written by Chris Morris and it was downloaded from https://github.com/hostilefork/whitespacers/blob/master/examples/fibonacci.ws

quine-2.ws.about: This quine is written by Benjamin Lerman and was downloaded from http://compsoc.dur.ac.uk/whitespace/quine-2.ws.

bf.wsa.about: A Brainfuck interpreter written in Whitespace.

collatz.wsa.about: Will output a Collaz sequence starting from a user provided number.

lib/math.wsa.about: Whitespace assembly library containing methods such as: pow, abs, max, min, sign, gcd, lcm, sqrt, neg, shr, shl.

lib/string.wsa.about:
Whitespace assembly library containing string manipulation functions:
* prints - print the string
* printMem - prints out a memory area with given length
* nl - print a newline character
* storeStr - store string at a given address
* printHeap - print the contents of the heap
* printStack - print the contents of the stack.

lib/alias.wsa.about: Contains aliases for compatibility with other Whitespace assembly languages.

lib/std.wsa.about: The standard library for the built-in Whitespace assembly. This file includes the whole library - do not worry, the optimizer will remove all unused code.

vm/bf.ws.about: A Brainfuck interpreter written compiled into Whitespace. To run a Brainfuck program open one and hit the run button.

vm/bf.wsa.about: A Brainfuck interpreter written in Whitespace assembly. To run a Brainfuck program open one and hit the run button.

wc/bf2wsa.wsa.about: Brainfuck to Whitespace assembly compiler written in Whitespace assembly. Just open a Brainfuck file and hit the compile button - the assembly is turned into Whitespace automatically.

wc/bf2wsa.ws.about: Brainfuck to Whitespace assembly compiler compiled into Whitespace. Just open a Brainfuck file and hit the compile button - the assembly is turned into Whitespace automatically.

hello.bf.about: Hello world Brainfuck implementation downloaded from https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brainfuck

vm/mal.wsa.about: A Malbolge interpreter written in Whitespace assembly. Inorder to run a Malbolge program open one (with .mal extension) in the editor and hit the run button. By default the compiled version is preferred by the IDE - if you want to to run specifically the assembly version then simply delete the compiled file.

vm/mal.ws.about: A compiled interpreter written in Malbolge. Inorder to run a Malbolge program open one (with .mal extension) in the editor and hit the run button.

hello.mal.about: A hello world implementation in Malbolge. Downloaded from https://github.com/nstarke/malbolge-examples

hello2.mal.about: A shorter version of hello world implementation in Malbolge. Downloaded from https://github.com/nstarke/malbolge-examples

cat.mal.about:
A cat program in Malbolge (this one does not stop on EOF; one which does is several orders of magnitude more complex)
Downloaded from https://esolangs.org/wiki/Malbolge.

99bottles.mal.about:
This Malbolge program is written by Hisashi Iizawa and was downloaded from http://99-bottles-of-beer.net/language-malbolge-995.html.

Running this huge Malbolge program using the interpreter written in Whitespace will take a long time, but eventually it will output the lyrics to the song 99 Bottles of Beer. This program was of great help in testing the interpreter - thank you!.
